    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-08-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="300"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-08-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1132.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inform you, with
                    regret, that the Department has received a telegram from the consul of the
                    United States at Manila announcing the death on the 2d instant of Mr. Walker,
                    Her Majesty’s consul at that port.</p>
                <p>I beg you to do me the favor to convey to your Government an expression of the
                    Department’s high appreciation of the very valuable services recently rendered
                    by Mr. Walker to this Government in looking after American interests in
                    Manila.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
